lass=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 04, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104fln1665703134854.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/fln1665703134854.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/fln1665703134854.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"fln1665703134854\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"fln1665703134854__uuf_list_411526\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Copy list data from a basic parameter or entity field.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"fln1665703134854__topic_d124511e1_d124512e1_d124513e1\">\n<div class=\"p\">\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104fln1665703134854_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"fln1665703134854__codeblock_bz3_nll_bwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">long uuf2list (UHACT hOpr, int seqNr, UHACT hList);</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"fln1665703134854__topic_d87827e1_d87828e1_d87829e1_d87830e1_d87831e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d248674e61\">Parameters</h2>\n<dl class=\"dl parml\" id=\"fln1665703134854__parml_ecz_4ll_bwb\">\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">hOpr</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">The handle to the operation or entity parameter</dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">seqNr</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">The sequence number of the basic parameter or entity field (sequence numbers\n                  start with 1)</dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">hList</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">The handle to a list that will be populated with data. The list must be created\n                  with <code class=\"ph codeph\">ulistnew</code>.</dd>\n</dl>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"fln1665703134854__topic_d87832e1_d87833e1_d87834e1_d87835e1_d87836e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d248674e103\">Return Values</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fln1665703134854__d5955e20\">For more information, see the \"Call-In API Return\n        Codes\" topic.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"fln1665703134854__topic_d87837e1_d87838e1_d87839e1_d87840e1_d87841e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d248674e112\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fln1665703134854__d5956e20\">Library:  <span class=\"ph filepath\">ucall</span></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"fln1665703134854__topic_d87842e1_d87843e1_d87844e1_d87845e1_d87846e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d248674e124\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fln1665703134854__p_d124544e1_d124545e1_d124546e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">uuf2list</code> copies list data from a basic parameter or entity field to the\n            specified list.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fln1665703134854__p_d124547e1_d124548e1_d124549e1\">This function is unconventional because it does not\n            return its output (the list) by reference. Instead, you must first create the list\n            yourself by calling <code class=\"ph codeph\">ulistnew</code>, and pass its handle (by value) to\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">uuf2list</code> in the parameter <code class=\"ph codeph\">hList</code>. After use, the\n            list should be freed by calling <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufreeh</code>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"fln1665703134854__section_xp2_tll_bwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d248674e151\">Example: ulistget and uuf2list</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The following example shows how to retrieve and process a list that was\n            returned as an OUT parameter by a 4GL operation. The operation GETLIST in service\n            TESTSRV is defined as follows:</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104fln1665703134854_html_1\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"fln1665703134854__codeblock_onj_5ll_bwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">operation getlist\nparams\nstring thelist : out;\nendparams\n\nputitem thelist, -1, \"One\"\nputitem thelist, -1, \"Two\"\nputitem thelist, -1, \"Three\"\nend</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\">The following 3GL code activates service GETLIST, retrieves the indexed\n            list, and loops through the items to print them out.</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104fln1665703134854_html_2\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"fln1665703134854__codeblock_swz_vll_bwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">#include &lt;h3gl.h&gt;\n#include &lt;stdio.h&gt;\n\nvoid get_itemlist ()\n{\nUHACT hEnv, hIn; /* Environment and instance handle */\nUHACT hOp; /* Operation handles for OP1 amd OP2 */\nlong actStatus, procErr; /* Activation status and procerr */\nUHACT hList; /* Item list handle */\nint i; /* Loop variable */\nUCHAR *pItem;\n\nueopen(&amp;hEnv); /* Get environment handle */\n/* Instantiate service TESTSVC */\nuinstnew (hEnv, (UCHAR *)\"TESTSVC\", 0, 0,\nUDEFAULT_COMM_MODE, 0, &amp;hIn, &amp;procErr);\n\n/* Instantiate operation GETLIST */\nuinstopr (hIn, (UCHAR *)\"GETLIST\", 0, &amp;hOp);\nuopract(hOp, &amp;actStatus, &amp;procErr); /* Activate the operation */\n\nulistnew(hEnv, &amp;hList); /* Create an item list */\nuuf2list(hOp, 1, hList); /* Get the list data */\n\ni=1;\n/* Loop through list items */\nwhile ( ulistget(hList, UITEM_OPTION_NONE,\ni, 0, &amp;pItem) == UACT_SUCCESS )\n{\nprintf(\"Item %d = '%s'\\n\", i, pItem); /* Print out item */\nunifree(hList, pItem); /* Free item data */\ni++;\n}\n\nuinstdel (hIn, 0); /* Destroy instance */\nufreeh (&amp;hList); /* Free list handle */\nufreeh (&amp;hOp); /* Free operation handle */\nufreeh (&amp;hIn); /* Free instance handle */\nufreeh (&amp;hEnv); /* Free environment handle */\n}</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\">This code prints out:</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104fln1665703134854_html_3\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"fln1665703134854__codeblock_pjc_yll_bwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">Item 1 = 'One'\nItem 2 = 'Two'\nItem 3 = 'Three'</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jhh1665702691902.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Call-In API Return Codes</a><p>Codes that can possibly be returned by functions from the 3GL call-in API are consistent with the values returned by the ProcScript function $procerror, unless noted otherwise.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/voy1665703134785.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>ulist2uf</a><p>Copy item list data to a basic parameter or entity field.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yvk1665703134983.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>ulistget</a><p>Get an item from an item list.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yia1665702692785.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>ulistnew</a><p>Create an item list.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527568\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527568\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "uuf2list Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 04, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Copy list data from a basic parameter or entity field. Explain this code long uuf2list (UHACT hOpr, int seqNr, UHACT hList); Copy Parameters hOpr The handle to the operation or entity parameter seqNr The sequence number of the basic parameter or entity field (sequence numbers start with 1) hList The handle to a list that will be populated with data. The list must be created with ulistnew . Return Values For more information, see the \"Call-In API Return Codes\" topic. Use Library: ucall Description uuf2list copies list data from a basic parameter or entity field to the specified list. This function is unconventional because it does not return its output (the list) by reference. Instead, you must first create the list yourself by calling ulistnew , and pass its handle (by value) to uuf2list in the parameter hList . After use, the list should be freed by calling ufreeh . Example: ulistget and uuf2list The following example shows how to retrieve and process a list that was returned as an OUT parameter by a 4GL operation. The operation GETLIST in service TESTSRV is defined as follows: Explain this code operation getlist params string thelist : out; endparams putitem thelist, -1, \"One\" putitem thelist, -1, \"Two\" putitem thelist, -1, \"Three\" end Copy The following 3GL code activates service GETLIST, retrieves the indexed list, and loops through the items to print them out. Explain this code #include <h3gl.h> #include <stdio.h> void get_itemlist () { UHACT hEnv, hIn; /* Environment and instance handle */ UHACT hOp; /* Operation handles for OP1 amd OP2 */ long actStatus, procErr; /* Activation status and procerr */ UHACT hList; /* Item list handle */ int i; /* Loop variable */ UCHAR *pItem; ueopen(&hEnv); /* Get environment handle */ /* Instantiate service TESTSVC */ uinstnew (hEnv, (UCHAR *)\"TESTSVC\", 0, 0, UDEFAULT_COMM_MODE, 0, &hIn, &procErr); /* Instantiate operation GETLIST */ uinstopr (hIn, (UCHAR *)\"GETLIST\", 0, &hOp); uopract(hOp, &actStatus, &procErr); /* Activate the operation */ ulistnew(hEnv, &hList); /* Create an item list */ uuf2list(hOp, 1, hList); /* Get the list data */ i=1; /* Loop through list items */ while ( ulistget(hList, UITEM_OPTION_NONE, i, 0, &pItem) == UACT_SUCCESS ) { printf(\"Item %d = '%s'\\n\", i, pItem); /* Print out item */ unifree(hList, pItem); /* Free item data */ i++; } uinstdel (hIn, 0); /* Destroy instance */ ufreeh (&hList); /* Free list handle */ ufreeh (&hOp); /* Free operation handle */ ufreeh (&hIn); /* Free instance handle */ ufreeh (&hEnv); /* Free environment handle */ } Copy This code prints out: Explain this code Item 1 = 'One' Item 2 = 'Two' Item 3 = 'Three' Copy Related Links Call-In API Return Codes Codes that can possibly be returned by functions from the 3GL call-in API are consistent with the values returned by the ProcScript function $procerror, unless noted otherwise. ulist2uf Copy item list data to a basic parameter or entity field. ulistget Get an item from an item list. ulistnew Create an item list. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}